02:28:57.360 --> 02:29:03.400
[Guest 1]: me and and maybe you watched it and the music didn't even sort of feel insistent to you.

02:29:03.400 --> 02:29:06.760
[Guest 1]: So, so it's two different people responding to it.

02:29:06.760 --> 02:29:12.400
[Guest 1]: To come back to what I was saying, I think even though, you know, a film that that might

02:29:12.400 --> 02:29:18.440
[Guest 1]: seem to you to be a case of a lot of spoon feeding the viewer, just making the viewer

02:29:18.440 --> 02:29:21.960
[Guest 1]: passive as you say, and you know, and just the film constantly telling you what to do.

02:29:21.960 --> 02:29:24.400
[Guest 1]: There is a part of participative process in that as well.

02:29:24.400 --> 02:29:28.200
[Guest 1]: Now, you know, if you look at if I look at some of my favourite masala Hindi films of

02:29:28.200 --> 02:29:33.360
[Guest 1]: a past era, including the big, brassy musical numbers and things, I feel like I'm part of

02:29:33.360 --> 02:29:37.840
[Guest 1]: participating in a different way if I if I see a lovely song sequence that I'm really

